702599f-a.title: Brooklyn: 18th Avenue - 66th Street
702599f-a.text:
Eighteenth Ave., east side, between 66th and 67th Streets, showing an
old home in which the West End Democratic Club held its meetings. The long
side of the house faced 67th Street. This building was demolished in late
1916 or early 1917.
About 1916.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODDUCED.
